Defendant Jovan T Mull in court with Attorney Eamon Collins Guerin.  Defendant Jovan T Mull in custody.  
Paul Leonard Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded. Parties indicate no corrections necessary to presentence investigation report.  Statements made by the Michelle W. (telephonically), state, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 35 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 451 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 25 YEARS.  
The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 10 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Substance Abuse Program.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment and complete any recommended counseling and/or follow-up care/treatment- take any medication prescribed;
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No contact with victim's immediate family members;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Therapy programming;
*Obtain/maintain part time employment;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs within 35 years- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

The Court ordered restitution payable in the stipulated amounts as follows: $2,000.00 to Crime Victim Compensation Program and $205.00 to Michelle W.  
The Court ordered all financial obligations and restitution to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds to be paid within 35 years.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.

Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms or body armor.  Defendant also advised because he has been convicted of a violent felony under Section 941.29, if he possesses a firearm within 5 years of completing this felony sentence, he will be subject to a mandatory 3 year initial confinement sentence.
Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  
Defendant advised of his right to appeal this sentence. 
